lds_0_about-facilities-fields-text',''),(178,60,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(179,60,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image',''),(180,60,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(181,60,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(182,60,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(183,60,'about-team',''),(184,60,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(185,7,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(186,7,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(187,7,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(188,7,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(189,7,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great-tasting beer. \r\n\r\nAs a member of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services – Haas has the global reach to offer the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(190,7,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(191,7,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','625'),(192,7,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(193,7,'about-overview','1'),(194,7,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(195,7,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(196,7,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(197,7,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a company that constantly evolves to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when a young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally become a reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(198,7,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(199,7,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(200,7,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(201,7,'about-history','4'),(202,7,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(203,7,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(204,7,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(205,7,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While John I. Haas buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600 acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team oversees the growth of the most sought-after hop varieties in the world. '),(206,7,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(207,7,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(208,7,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(209,7,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(210,7,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(211,7,'about-team','a:14:{i:0;s:3:\"925\";i:1;s:3:\"205\";i:2;s:3:\"220\";i:3;s:3:\"219\";i:4;s:3:\"217\";i:5;s:3:\"917\";i:6;s:3:\"204\";i:7;s:3:\"923\";i:8;s:3:\"915\";i:9;s:3:\"913\";i:10;s:3:\"218\";i:11;s:3:\"921\";i:12;s:3:\"974\";i:13;s:3:\"216\";}'),(212,7,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(213,61,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(214,61,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(215,61,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(216,61,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(217,61,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are a breeder — creator of some of today’s most popular hop varieties. We are a test brewery – our Innovations Brewery is a state-of-the-art facility where you can experiment with new recipes, techniques and varieties. We are an resource – home to the Hops Academy where brewers can get a better understanding of the complexity of hops. We are partners – fellow beer lovers who understand why you need flexible and creative contracts. But most of all, we are an innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about providing you with the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew great beer. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(218,61,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(219,61,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image',''),(220,61,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(221,61,'about-overview','1'),(222,61,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(223,61,'about-history_0_about-history-header',''),(224,61,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(225,61,'about-history_0_about-history-left',''),(226,61,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(227,61,'about-history_0_about-history-right',''),(228,61,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(229,61,'about-history','1'),(230,61,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(231,61,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header',''),(232,61,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(233,61,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text',''),(234,61,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(235,61,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image',''),(236,61,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(237,61,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(238,61,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(239,61,'about-team',''),(240,61,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(241,62,'_wp_attached_file','2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg'),(242,62,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:297;s:6:\"height\";i:141;s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"prohibition-beyond2-150x141.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:141;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"foca