com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(382,72,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(383,72,'about-history','4'),(384,72,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(385,72,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(386,72,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(387,72,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I Haas company commissions many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Yakima valley, we also grow, breed and process hops on our own Yakima Golding farm. This 1,400 acre facility was the original farm purchased by John I. Haas back in 1931 when he first came to the Yakima valley. It features trellised farmland for growing the hops as well as elaborate picking machines, hop kilns and baling operations.\r\n\r\nAll this is supported by highly qualified, innovative and experienced farm management personnel, supporting the production of the major U.S. hop varieties. Haas benefits from a dedicated and experienced seasonal workforce that is provided modern housing facilities for the time they are with us during the growing season and harvest.'),(388,72,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(389,72,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(390,72,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(391,72,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(392,72,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(393,72,'about-team',''),(394,72,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(395,7,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(396,7,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(397,7,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(398,7,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(399,7,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(400,7,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(401,7,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(402,7,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(403,7,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(404,7,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(405,7,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.'),(406,7,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(407,7,'about-history_3_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(408,7,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(409,73,'_edit_last','1'),(410,73,'_edit_lock','1418675425:1'),(411,76,'varieties-header','126 WAYS TO CREATE\r\nYOUR NEXT GREAT BREW'),(412,76,'_varieties-header','field_548f1483f6aa2'),(413,76,'varieties-text','Great beer begins with great hops. That’s not telling you anything you don’t know. But what you may not know is that Haas can supply you with just about every type of hop from anywhere in the world. Whether you’re looking for the freshest alphas or the most intriguing aromas, Haas is your source. Use the box to the right to browse our varieties. They’re arranged alphabetically, but you can also filter by geography and flavor profile.'),(414,76,'_varieties-text','field_548f14c11611e'),(415,9,'varieties-header','126 varieties. Unlimited possibilities.'),(416,9,'_varieties-header','field_548f1483f6aa2'),(417,9,'varieties-text','Great beer begins with great hops. That’s not telling you anything you don’t know. But what you may not know is that Haas can supply you with just about every type of hop from anywhere in the world. Whether you’re looking for the freshest alphas or the most intriguing aromas, Haas is your source. Use the box to browse our varieties. They’re arranged alphabetically, but you can also filter by region. '),(418,9,'_varieties-text','field_548f14c11611e'),(419,77,'_edit_last','1'),(420,77,'_edit_lock','1422039524:1'),(421,11,'products-header','HOP PRODUCTS THAT FLAVOR YOUR BEER.\r\nAND FEED YOUR IMAGINATION.'),(422,11,'_products-header','field_548f155279e5d'),(423,11,'products-description','Beer is all about flavor. And flavor is all about hops. So whatever flavor you’re trying to create, Haas has the hop products to help make it happen. From classic forms of whole hop cones, hop pellets and CO2 extracts to our more advanced, innovative hop products that add specific flavor and functionality, Ha