tion of family ownership. Prior to his appointment as CEO, Alex served as Executive Vice President of Supply Chain Management where he was responsible for expanding the strong, multi-generational grower relationships John I. Haas continues to enjoy in the United States. Earlier roles included oversight of the company’s significant hop farm production as well as key customer accounts.\r\n\r\nAlex holds a Bachelor of Science in General Agriculture from the University of Maryland and a Master of Science in Soil Science from Oregon State University.'),(1213,205,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1214,205,'team-moment','when our innovations lead to customer innovations.'),(1215,205,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1217,216,'_edit_last','6'),(1218,216,'_edit_lock','1438096093:6'),(1220,216,'team-position','VP Sales & Marketing'),(1221,216,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1222,216,'team-description','David Thurston joined John I. Haas in April of 2012 and oversees all sales and marketing activity for the company. In addition to his responsibilities at Haas, David is a member of the Haas Leadership Team and the Barth-Haas Group Sales and Marketing Leadership Team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Haas, David worked for Cargill, Inc., holding various positions in Sales and Marketing, Strategy and General Management over a 25-year career in grain processing, meat processing and biotech businesses.\r\n\r\nDavid is a graduate of the University of Denver and has an MBA from the Fuqua School of Business at Duke University.'),(1223,216,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1224,216,'team-moment','when a brewer realizes we know beer as well as we know hops.'),(1225,216,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1226,217,'_edit_last','6'),(1227,217,'_edit_lock','1438096149:6'),(1229,217,'team-position','VP BetaTec Hop Products'),(1230,217,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1231,217,'team-description','John Forte joined John I. Haas in September of 2014 and oversees all sales, research &amp; development, and marketing activity for the BetaTec division globally. In addition to his responsibilities at BetaTec, John is a member of the Haas Senior Leadership Team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Haas, John worked for Pure Circle Ltd., holding the position of Vice President Sales of North America, Japan, Australia/New Zealand. John’s career spans over a 20-year period in the global food industry.\r\n\r\nJohn is a graduate of Roosevelt University and has an MBA from Rosemont College along with a Masters in European Food Marketing from St. Joseph’s University in Philadelphia, PA.'),(1232,217,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1233,217,'team-moment','when we put hops to work in innovative ways. '),(1234,217,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1235,218,'_edit_last','6'),(1236,218,'_edit_lock','1438187808:6'),(1238,218,'team-position','VP Supply Chain & Purchasing'),(1239,218,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1240,218,'team-description','Pete Mahony has been Director of Supply Chain at Haas since 2012. But hops have been a part of Pete’s life for much longer than that. Pete grew up in the hop growing area of St. Paul, Oregon, and worked for a hop grower during summers while attending Oregon State University. In 1987 he began working for John Barth &amp; Sohn in Hubbard, Oregon, as a hop buyer and also as a plant manager for Westnut in Dundee, an affiliate company of Haas involved in hazelnut products. In 1994 Pete moved to Yakima to work at the John I. Haas Extract Plant as an assistant to Jim Stoffer, VP of Operations. When Jim retired in 2000, Pete moved up to a managerial position and continued in that role until being promoted to his current position. Pete also oversees the farming and hop purchasing areas of John I. Haas.'),(1241,218,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1242,218,'team-moment','when everyone has what they need, when they need it.'),(1243,218,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1244,219,'_edit_last','6'),(1245,219,'_edit_lock','1438096306:6'),(1247,219,'team-position','CFO'),(1248,219,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1249,219,'team-description','Tom Davis has served as John I. Haas’s Chief Financial Officer since 2004.  Tom has ultimate responsibility over all finance, information technology, human resource and legal functions.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Haas, Tom held several senior finance and accounting positions including CFO of Xybernaut Corporation and Director of Finance at MeriStar Hospitality Corporation. Tom began his career as an auditor at Deloitte &amp; Touche.\r\n\r\nTom is a Certified Public Accountant and graduated with honors from James Madison University (BBA 1991).  He serves as a Trustee for the Oregon College of Art and Craft.'),(1250,219,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1251,219,'team-moment','when money never gets in the way of innovation.'),(1252,219,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1253,220,'_edit_last','6'),(1254,220,'_edit_lock','1438096251:6'),(1256,220,'team-position','VP Finance'),(1257,220,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1258,220,'team-description','As our Corporate Controller, Stephanie oversees all accounting, analysis and office administration functions for Haas as well as our various joint ventures and US affiliates. In her analysis role, Stephanie draws upon her 25 years of hops experience to ensure the Company’s strategies and activities are on solid financial footing. Stephanie has lived in the Yakima Valley for 35 years and has been with Haas since she graduated from Washington State University in 1990 with a BA in Accounting. She is also a licensed Certified Public Accountant.'),(1259,220,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1260,220,'team-moment','when all business decisions are financially sound.'),(1261,220,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1262,221,'_edit_last','6'),(1263,221,'_edit_lock','1444915085:6'),(1265,221,'team-position','VP Technical & Innovations'),(1266,221,'_team-position','field_54908460ead1d'),(1267,221,'team-description','Scott, a native of Canada, has been Technical Director of Haas since 2007 and is responsible for the Company’s quality, R&amp;D and brewing programs. He attended the University of Alberta where he received two Bachelor degrees and a Ph.D. in Food Chemistry. He also has an MBA from the University of Washington.\r\n\r\nScott began his career in the brewing and malting industry in 1994 as a postdoctoral scientist with Canadian Malting.  While at Canadian Malting he worked on various R&amp;D projects related to malt quality.  Scott joined Haas in 1999 in the role of Technical Projects Leader. During his tenure here, he has been involved in various technical and business development projects including the development of the Company’s quality, environmental and food safety management systems.'),(1268,221,'_team-description','field_54908498ead1e'),(1269,221,'team-moment','when hop chemistry + brewing process = [wow]<sup>2</sup>.'),(1270,221,'_team-moment','field_549084bbead1f'),(1271,222,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(1272,222,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(1273,222,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(1274,222,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(1275,222,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are a breeder — creator of some of today’s most popular hop varieties. We are a test brewery – our Innovations Brewery is a state-of-the-art facility where you can experiment with new recipes, techniques and varieties. We are an resource – home to the Hops Academy where brewers can get a better understanding of the complexity of hops. We are partners – fellow beer lovers who understand why you need flexible and creative contracts. But most of all, we are an innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about providing you with the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew great beer. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(1276,222,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(1277,222,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','65'),(1278,222,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(1279,222,'about-overview','1'),(1280,222,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(1281,222,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(1282,222,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1283,222,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(1284,222,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1285,222,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – the careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a company that is constantly evolving to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I, as his friends called him) and tried to recruit him into joining his hop business. Instead, John I decided to start his own hop business — in America.'),(1286,222,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1287,222,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(1288,222,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1289,222,'about-history_1_about-history-header','PROHIBITION AND BEYOND'),(1290,222,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1291,222,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(1292,222,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1293,222,'about-history_1_about-history-left','Despite a rocky start, which included both World War I and, of course, Prohibition, his hop business grew because of his initiative to look for customers outside the United States. In particular, Haas built strong relationships with Canadian brewers who, not surprisingly, were benefiting greatly from American Prohibition. In 1925, John I acquired his first hop farm in the Fraser Valley of British Columbia (which eventually grew to 1,300 acres).\r\n\r\nThen in 1931, Haas sensed a change in what the world’s brewers were looking for. He bought a bought a farm in Yakima, Washington and instead of growing Clusters and Fuggles hops (which were seeded and of bad picking quality), he implemented a program to reduce the seed content and improve the picking quality of his hops. He named the hop, and his farm, Yakima Golding and the brewers responded in droves. This innovation, the first of many, led to rapid growth and Haas became the world’s largest private hop grower in the world with 25 farms and almost 4,000 acres.'),(1294,222,'_about-history_1_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1295,222,'about-history_1_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond\" width=\"293\" height=\"149\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond2\" width=\"297\" height=\"141\" /></a>'),(1296,222,'_about-history_1_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1297,222,'about-history_2_about-history-header','HAAS AND BARTH. '),(1298,222,'_about-history_2_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1299,222,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(1300,222,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1301,222,'about-history_2_about-history-left','For the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America but faced increasing pressure abroad from the Joh Barth &amp; Sons, a German hop company based in Nuremberg that began operations as far back as 1794. At times, the competition was fierce with each company used its expertise and innovation to try to get an edge on the other. But after Fred Haas took over for John I in 1964, the two companies realized they had more in common than the flower they grew – the drive for innovation, the obsession with quality and the core belief that while their fine hops got their customers to come, but it was service that got them to come back. So when the time came for Fred to step down as President, he approached _______ about buying his company. The result was that in 1978, John I Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.'),(1302,222,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1303,222,'about-history_2_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(1304,222,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1305,222,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\n100 YEARS YOUNG ONE'),(1306,222,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1307,222,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(1308,222,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1309,222,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained its passion for innovation. In the 1990’s, the Haas hop breeding program brought the hop varieties Chelan and Millennium into the world. More recently, Haas partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra as Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5 hectoliter experimental brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our'),(1310,222,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1311,222,'about-history_3_about-history-right','brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated its 100th anniversary. And while John I might have trouble recognizing some of today’s modern facilities, we are certain he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service that he set the standard for from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(1312,222,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1313,222,'about-history','4'),(1314,222,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(1315,222,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(1316,222,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(1317,222,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I Haas company commissions many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Yakima valley, we also grow, breed and process hops on our own Yakima Golding farm. This 1,400 acre facility was the original farm purchased by John I. Haas back in 1931 when he first came to the Yakima valley. It features trellised farmland for growing the hops as well as elaborate picking machines, hop kilns and baling operations.\r\n\r\nAll this is supported by highly qualified, innovative and experienced farm management personnel, supporting the production of the major U.S. hop varieties. Haas benefits from a dedicated and experienced seasonal workforce that is provided modern housing facilities for the time they are with us during the growing season and harvest.'),(1318,222,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(1319,222,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(1320,222,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(1321,222,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(1322,222,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(1323,222,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"221\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"219\";}'),(1324,222,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(1325,223,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(1326,223,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(1327,223,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(1328,223,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(1329,223,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are a breeder — creator of some of today’s most popular hop varieties. We are a test brewery – our Innovations Brewery is a state-of-the-art facility where you can experiment with new recipes, techniques and varieties. We are an resource – home to the Hops Academy where brewers can get a better understanding of the complexity of hops. We are partners – fellow beer lovers who understand why you need flexible and creative contracts. But most of all, we are an innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about providing you with the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew great beer. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(1330,223,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(1331,223,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','65'),(1332,223,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(1333,223,'about-overview','1'),(1334,223,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(1335,223,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(1336,223,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1337,223,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(1338,223,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1339,223,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – the careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a company that is constantly evolving to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I, as his friends called him) and tried to recruit him into joining his hop business. Instead, John I decided to start his own hop business — in America.'),(1340,223,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1341,223,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(1342,223,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1343,223,'about-history_1_about-history-header','PROHIBITION AND BEYOND'),(1344,223,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1345,223,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(1346,223,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1347,223,'about-history_1_about-history-left','Despite a rocky start, which included both World War I and, of course, Prohibition, his hop business grew because of his initiative to look for customers outside the United States. In particular, Haas built strong relationships with Canadian brewers who, not surprisingly, were benefiting greatly from American Prohibition. In 1925, John I acquired his first hop farm in the Fraser Valley of British Columbia (which eventually grew to 1,300 acres).\r\n\r\nThen in 1931, Haas sensed a change in what the world’s brewers were looking for. He bought a bought a farm in Yakima, Washington and instead of growing Clusters and Fuggles hops (which were seeded and of bad picking quality), he implemented a program to reduce the seed content and improve the picking quality of his hops. He named the hop, and his farm, Yakima Golding and the brewers responded in droves. This innovation, the first of many, led to rapid growth and Haas became the world’s largest private hop grower in the world with 25 farms and almost 4,000 acres.'),(1348,223,'_about-history_1_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1349,223,'about-history_1_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond\" width=\"293\" height=\"149\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond2\" width=\"297\" height=\"141\" /></a>'),(1350,223,'_about-history_1_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1351,223,'about-history_2_about-history-header','HAAS AND BARTH. '),(1352,223,'_about-history_2_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1353,223,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(1354,223,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1355,223,'about-history_2_about-history-left','For the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America but faced increasing pressure abroad from the Joh Barth &amp; Sons, a German hop company based in Nuremberg that began operations as far back as 1794. At times, the competition was fierce with each company used its expertise and innovation to try to get an edge on the other. But after Fred Haas took over for John I in 1964, the two companies realized they had more in common than the flower they grew – the drive for innovation, the obsession with quality and the core belief that while their fine hops got their customers to come, but it was service that got them to come back. So when the time came for Fred to step down as President, he approached _______ about buying his company. The result was that in 1978, John I Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.'),(1356,223,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1357,223,'about-history_2_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(1358,223,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1359,223,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\n100 YEARS YOUNG ONE'),(1360,223,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(1361,223,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(1362,223,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(1363,223,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained its passion for innovation. In the 1990’s, the Haas hop breeding program brought the hop varieties Chelan and Millennium into the world. More recently, Haas partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra as Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5 hectoliter experimental brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our'),(1364,223,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(1365,223,'about-history_3_about-history-right','brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated its 100th anniversary. And while John I might have trouble recognizing some of today’s modern facilities, we are certain he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service that he set the standard for from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(1366,223,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(1367,223,'about-history','4'),(1368,223,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(1369,223,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(1370,223,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(1371,223,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I Haas company commissions many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Yakima valley, we also grow, breed and process hops on our own Yakima Golding farm. This 1,400 acre facility was the original farm purchased by John I. Haas back in 1931 when he first came to the Yakima valley. It features trellised farmland for growing the hops as well as elaborate picking machines, hop kilns and baling operations.\r\n\r\nAll this is supported by highly qualified, innovative and experienced farm management personnel, supporting the production of the major U.S. hop varieties. Haas benefits from a dedicated and experienced seasonal workforce that is provided modern housing facilities for the time they are with us during the growing season and harvest.'),(1372,223,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(1373,223,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(1374,223,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(1375,223,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(1376,223,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(1377,223,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(1378,223,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(1379,224,'_edit_last','1'),(1380,224,'_edit_lock','1438283368:1'),(1387,231,'_edit_lock','1422293055:1'),(1388,231,'_edit_last','1'),(1389,23,'career-open-positions','a:4:{i:0;s:4:\"1041\";i:1;s:3:\"941\";i:2;s:4:\"1010\";i:3;s:4:\"1029\";}'),(1390,23,'_career-open-positions','field_5491aee343ab3'),(1394,235,'_wp_attached_file','2014/12/event-pic.png'),(1395,235,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:508;s:6:\"height\";i:193;s:4:\"file\";s:21:\"2014/12/event-pic.png\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:21:\"event-pic-150x150.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:21:\"event-pic-300x113.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(1398,237,'resources-header','INNOVATION, INSPIRATION AND COLLABORATION'),(1399,237,'_resources-header','field_548f4536d88a0'),(1400,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','INNOVATIONS BREWERY FEATURES:'),(1401,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(1402,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','<ul>\r\n	<li>2.5 hl 5 vessel state-of-the-art brew house with 10 and 30 liter hop dosing vessels</li>\r\n	<li>A brew house control system with customizable recipe and extensive data collection</li>\r\n	<li>21 unitank fermentation and conditioning system capable of 1.25 and 2.5 hl brews</li>\r\n	<li>Beer filtration capabilities including diatomaceous earth and depth filter</li>\r\n	<li>Krones bottling system with double pre-evacuation &amp; CO2 pressurization</li>\r\n	<li>Precision malt milling (4 roll) and adjunct preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Laboratory analysis for hops and beer</li>\r\n</ul>'),(1403,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(1404,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','130'),(1405,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(1406,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','CREATIVITY, MEET REPEATABILITY, FLEXIBILITY AND SCALABILITY.'),(1407,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(1408,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','From the company that brought you the HBC varieties Citra® and Mosaic® comes another innovation — the Haas Innovations Brewery, a world-class brewing and research facility in Yakima, Washington that gives you the ability to try out new hops, new recipes and new visions in a totally controllable, repeatable and creative environment. Creating new and commercially successful beers requires access to a brewing facility that provides repeatable, flexible and scalable brewing capabilities. And that’s exactly what you get with the Innovations Brewery.<strong><a href=\"http://shotgunflatdev.com/ongoing/HAAS3/#\">READ MORE</a></strong>'),(1409,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(1410,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','128'),(1411,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(1412,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','IMAGINE WHAT YOU COULD BREW.'),(1413,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(1414,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, we celebrate the passion and creativity of those dedicated to brewing great beer. But we also know that dedication can only get you so far. Creating new and commercially successful beers requires access to a brewing facility that provides repeatable, flexible and scalable brewing capabilities. It starts with our state-of-the-art research facility that provides the sophisticated equipment and control system that allows you to refine a recipe and repeat it batch after batch. Next comes flexibility — the key to innovation. The Haas Innovations Brewery offers you a highly controlled, scientific environment in which to brew, test and adjust your recipes to get the perfect brew. Finally, there’s scalability. Our research brewery provides an unparalleled pilot-scale brewing experience, which means you can reduce the time and uncertainty often associated with new brews and get your next brewing creation to market faster and more efficiently.'),(1415,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(1416,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','127'),(1417,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(1418,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','HERE’S TO YOUR SUCCESS'),(1419,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(1420,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, our mission is your success. And our Innovations Brewery is designed to help you achieve it. Whether you’re looking to test the latest hop variety, ingredient, recipe or equipment, our research brewery is here to fast track your innovation. In addition to simply giving you a place to brew, our state-of-the-art laboratory gives you the advantage of the latest hop and beer analysis technology. You also get the experience and expertise of our technical staff and master brewers who help you get the most out of the product development process. To learn more or to reserve a brewing session, call 509-469-4000. And get ready to test, tweak, taste and toast your next great brew.'),(1421,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(1422,237,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','129'),(1423,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(1424,237,'resources-innovations-brewery','4'),(1425,237,'_resources-innovations-brewery','field_548f47c0d88a1'),(1426,237,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','HOPS. THERE’S MORE\r\nTHAN MEETS THE NOSE.'),(1427,237,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','field_548f487dd88a6'),(1428,237,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','It seems like the more you know about hops, the more there is to learn. That’s the thinking behind the Barth-Haas Hops Academy — a formal training program for brewers designed to open up a world of possibilities in the use, effects, and impact of this special brewing ingredient. In addition to helping brewers develop distinctive high-quality beers, the Hops Academy helps you improve process efficiencies and reduce waste.\r\n\r\nThe Hops Academy helps both new, experienced and even master brewers understand more about the complexities of hops and the way they interact with each other — as well as other beer ingredients — to create unique styles, flavors and aromas. To learn more about the Barth-Haas Hops Academy or to reserve a spot in an upcoming session, please visit <a href=\"http://shotgunflatdev.com/ongoing/HAAS3/#\">http://www.hopsacademy.com/en</a>'),(1429,237,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','field_548f48a2d88a7'),(1430,237,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','131'),(1431,237,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','field_548f48d8d88a8'),(1432,237,'resources-hops-academy','1'),(1433,237,'_resources-hops-academy','field_548f484fd88a5'),(1434,237,'resources-other_0_resources-other-link','http://www.barthhaasgroup.com/de/'),(1435,237,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(1436,237,'resources-other_0_resources-other-image','132'),(1437,237,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(1438,237,'resources-other_0_resources-other-header','BARTH-HAAS GROUP'),(1439,237,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(1440,237,'resources-other_0_resources-other-text','Barth-Haas Group is the world’s largest supplier of hop products and services. The group is family owned and is active on all continents, having offices and operations in Germany, the United States, United Kingdom, Australia and China. Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group.'),(1441,237,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(1442,237,'resources-other_1_resources-other-link','http://www.asbcnet.org/Pages/default.aspx'),(1443,237,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(1444,237,'resources-other_1_resources-other-image','133'),(1445,237,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(1446,237,'resources-other_1_resources-other-header','AMERICAN SOCIETY OF BREWING CHEMISTS'),(1447,237,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(1448,237,'resources-other_1_resources-other-text','The American Society of Brewing Chemists in an internationally recognized nonprofit scientific organization founded in 1934 to improve and bring uniformity to the brewing industry on a technical level. Today, ASBC is represented by individual and corporate members worldwide representing large and small brewers, consultants, government agencies, academics, distillers, vintners and those working in allied industries.'),(1449,237,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(1450,237,'resources-other','2'),(1451,237,'_resources-other','field_548f48e1d88a9'),(1452,240,'home-slider-overlay_0_home-slider-overlay-header','HERE’S TO THE MOMENTS'),(145