'field_548f0e74607f3'),(2411,286,'about-history_3_about-history-right','to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(2412,286,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(2413,286,'about-history','4'),(2414,286,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(2415,286,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(2416,286,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(2417,286,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(2418,286,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(2419,286,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(2420,286,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(2421,286,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(2422,286,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(2423,286,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(2424,286,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(2425,287,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(2426,287,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(2427,287,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(2428,287,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(2429,287,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, and a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great tasting beer. Whether you’re brewing 100 barrels or 100 million, Haas has the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(2430,287,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(2431,287,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','65'),(2432,287,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(2433,287,'about-overview','1'),(2434,287,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(2435,287,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(2436,287,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(2437,287,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(2438,287,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(2439,287,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a constantly evolving company to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally come to reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(2440,287,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(2441,287,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(2442,287,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(2443,287,'about-history_1_about-history-header','PERSEVERENCE AGAINST ALL ODDS'),(2444,287,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(2445,287,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(2446,287,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(2447,287,'about-history_1_about-history-left','1914 was all but a fortunate choice of year to found a company. It was the beginning of World War I, which was followed by Prohibition and Depression – all not conducive to support a start-up hop business. But despite all odds, his business grew b