artners_0_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(3688,569,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-more','Coming up with new aromas and flavors is a big part of what Haas contributes to the world brewing community. And one of the key contributors to these creations is our long-time master hop breeder, Gene Probasco. Gene and his agronomic team oversee more than 30 acres of experimental hops just waiting to be discovered.  The Hop Breeding Company conducts about 50 crosses of male and female hop parents each year, resulting in more than 20,000 offspring, all potentially becoming a commercial variety someday in the future.  While only a handful make it to an elite status and get christened with a name instead of a number, Gene and the Hop Breeding Company are proud parents who will stop at nothing for the good of their offspring.'),(3689,569,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(3690,569,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-link','http://www.lnf.com.br/'),(3691,569,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-link','field_548f4fd04dd58'),(3692,569,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-image','300'),(3693,569,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-image','field_548f502d4dd59'),(3694,569,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-header','Growing our knowledge and our reach'),(3695,569,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-header','field_548f50394dd5a'),(3696,569,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-text','At Haas, we are always looking to enhance the quality of the hops we grow through better technology, processes and efficiencies. That’s why we partner with LNF Latino Americana. Founded in 1987 and active in various biotech industries, LNF is a family owned and operated company that was built on the commitment to deliver highly qualified technical support to companies looking for high product quality and process optimization.  '),(3697,569,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(3698,569,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-more','The Brewing division of LNF specializes in hops and works closely with the Barth-Haas Group to develop our presence in the Brazilian market through a very close technical and commercial cooperation. '),(3699,569,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(3700,569,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-link','http://www.wvhops.us/index.php?p=home'),(3701,569,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-link','field_548f4fd04dd58'),(3702,569,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-image','144'),(3703,569,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-image','field_548f502d4dd59'),(3704,569,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-header',' You don’t have to be big to get Haas hops. But you do have to think big.'),(3705,569,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-header','field_548f50394dd5a'),(3706,569,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-text','Just because you’re a small brewery, doesn’t mean you shouldn’t be able to get your hands on high quality Haas hops. And thanks to our partnership with Willamette Valley Hops LLC, you can. '),(3707,569,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(3708,569,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-more','Willamette Valley Hops is an Oregon-based family-owned premium hop distributer, which specializes in the special needs of the craft industry.  Located in the heart of Oregon’s Willamette Valley hop growing region, Bruce Wolf, the company’s founder and CEO, leads a passionate sales team and production staff to provide over 50 different domestic and foreign hop varieties to brewers worldwide. The partnership between John I. Haas and Willamette Valley Hops provides an effective and efficient means to give small brewers access to the best hops in the world.'),(3709,569,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(3710,569,'partners-partners','3'),(3711,569,'_partners-partners','field_548f4fab4dd57'),(3712,570,'_wp_attached_file','2014/12/A