le, repeatable and creative environment. Creating new and commercially successful beers requires access to a brewing facility that provides repeatable, flexible and scalable brewing capabilities. And that’s exactly what you get with the Innovations Brewery.'),(4676,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(4677,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','128'),(4678,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(4679,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','IMAGINE WHAT YOU COULD BREW.'),(4680,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(4681,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, we celebrate the passion and creativity of those dedicated to brewing great beer. And our research brewery is one of the ways we help that creativity happen. It starts with our sophisticated, state-of-the-art equipment and control system that allows you to refine a recipe and repeat it batch after batch. Next comes flexibility — the key to innovation. The Haas Innovations Brewery offers you a highly controlled, scientific environment in which to brew, test and adjust your recipes to get the perfect brew. Finally, there’s scalability. Our research brewery provides an unparalleled scalable brewing experience, which means you can reduce the time and uncertainty often associated with new brews and get your next brewing creation to market faster and more efficiently.'),(4682,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(4683,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','127'),(4684,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(4685,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','HERE’S TO YOUR SUCCESS'),(4686,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(4687,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, our mission is your success. Whether you’re looking to test one of our new varieties or one of your latest recipes, the Haas Innovations Brewery will help you achieve it. The Haas research brewery also allows you to test our new products and see how we can deliver the same great flavors you seek without having to use as many hops (or dollars, for that matter). In addition to giving you a place to brew, our research brewery includes a state-of-the-art laboratory that gives you the advantage of the latest hop and beer analysis technology. You also get the experience and expertise of our technical staff and brewmaster Virgil McDonald who help you get the most out of the product development process. To learn more or to reserve a brewing session, call 509-469-4000<strong>.</strong> And get ready to test, tweak, taste and toast your next great brew.'),(4688,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(4689,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','129'),(4690,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(4691,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','INNOVATIONS BREWERY FEATURES:'),(4692,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(4693,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','<ul>\r\n	<li><em>2.5 hl 5 vessel state-of-the-art brew house with 10 and 30 liter hop dosing vessels</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>A brew house control system with customizable recipe and extensive data collection</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>21 unitank fermentation and conditioning system capable of 1.25 and 2.5 hl brews</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Beer filtration capabilities including diatomaceous earth and depth filter</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Krones bottling system with double pre-evacuation &amp; CO2 pressurization</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Precision malt milling (4 roll) and adjunct preparation</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Laboratory analysis for hops and beer</em></li>\r\n</ul>'),(4694,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(4695,659,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','130'),(4696,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(4697,659,'resources-innovations-brewery','4'),(4698,659,'_resources-innovations-brewery','field_548f47c0d88a1'),(4699,659,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','HOPS. THERE’S MORE\r\nTHAN MEETS THE NOSE.'),(4700,659,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','field_548f487dd88a6'),(4701,659,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','It seems like the more you know about hops, the more there is to learn. That’s the thinking behind the Barth-Haas Hops Academy — a formal training program for brewers designed to open up a world of possibilities in the use, effects, and impact of this special brewing ingredient. In addition to helping brewers develop distinctive high-quality beers, the Hops Academy helps you improve process efficiencies and reduce waste.\r\n\r\nThe Hops Academy helps both new, experienced and even master brewers understand more about the complexities of hops and the way they interact with each other — as well as other beer ingredients — to create unique styles, flavors and aromas. To learn more about the Barth-Haas Hops Academy or to reserve a spot in an upcoming session, please visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hopsacademy.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.hopsacademy.com/en</a>'),(4702,659,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','field_548f48a2d88a7'),(4703,659,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','131'),(4704,659,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','field_548f48d8d88a8'),(4705,659,'resources-hops-academy','1'),(4706,659,'_resources-hops-academy','field_548f484fd88a5'),(4707,659,'resources-other_0_resources-other-link','http://www.barthhaasgroup.com/en/'),(4708,659,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(4709,659,'resources-other_0_resources-other-image','132'),(4710,659,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(4711,659,'resources-other_0_resources-other-header','BARTH-HAAS GROUP'),(4712,659,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(4713,659,'resources-other_0_resources-other-text','Barth-Haas Group is the world’s largest supplier of hop products and services.  The group is family owned and is active on all continents, having offices and operations in Germany, the United States, United Kingdom, Australia and China.  Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group.\r\n<a  target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com\">www.BarthHaasGroup.com</a>'),(4714,659,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(4715,659,'resources-other_1_resources-other-link','http://www.asbcnet.org/Pages/default.aspx'),(4716,659,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(4717,659,'resources-other_1_resources-other-image','133'),(4718,659,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(4719,659,'resources-other_1_resources-other-header','AMERICAN SOCIETY OF BREWING CHEMISTS'),(4720,659,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(4721,659,'resources-other_1_resources-other-text','The American Society of Brewing Chemists in an internationally recognized nonprofit scientific organization founded in 1934 to improve and bring uniformity to the brewing industry on a technical level. Today, ASBC is represented by individual and corporate members worldwide representing large and small brewers, consultants, government agencies, academics, distillers, vintners and those working in allied industries.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.asbcnet.org\" >www.asbcnet.org</a>'),(4722,659,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(4723,659,'resources-other_2_resources-other-link',''),(4724,659,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(4725,659,'resources-other_2_resources-other-image','246'),(4726,659,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(4727,659,'resources-other_2_resources-other-header','MASTER BREWERS ASSOCIATION OF THE AMERICAS'),(4728,659,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(4729,659,'resources-other_2_resources-other-text','The Master Brewers Association of the Americas (MBAA) is a nonprofit professional, scientific organization dedicated to advance, support, and encourage scientific research into brewing malt beverages and related industries and to make that research available to the public through conventions, discussion groups, journals, publications and seminars.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.mbaa.com\" >www.mbaa.com</a>'),(4730,659,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(4731,659,'resources-other_3_resources-other-link',''),(4732,659,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(4733,659,'resources-other_3_resources-other-image','247'),(4734,659,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(4735,659,'resources-other_3_resources-other-header','OREGON STATE UNIVERSITY'),(4736,659,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(4737,659,'resources-other_3_resources-other-text','Haas works closely in association with the Food Science and Technology section of the Oregon State University College of Agricultural Sciences.  Dr. Tom Shellhammer leads the OSU work in brewing science and technolo