7,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(4939,667,'about-history_2_about-history-left','Over the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America as it transitioned to the next generation. Fred Haas took over from John I. in 1964 and continued his quest of delivering quality hops to brewers around the world. During Fred’s time at the helm of the company, Haas expanded its product portfolio into extracts, which laid the foundation for innovative refined hop products for the next decades. It was the US processing capabilities of Haas that peeked the interest of another market leader, namely Joh. Barth &amp; Sohn, Germany, under the leadership of Henry Barth. As much as Henry Barth and John I. were the fiercest of competitors, Fred Haas was able to find common ground and, having no children of his own, saw a continuation of his company in the hands of the Barth family that started in the hop business already in 1794.'),(4940,667,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(4941,667,'about-history_2_about-history-right','The result was that in 1977, John I. Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(4942,667,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(4943,667,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(4944,667,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(4945,667,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(4946,667,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(4947,667,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5-hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters'),(4948,667,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(4949,667,'about-history_3_about-history-right','to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(4950,667,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(4951,667,'about-history','4'),(4952,667,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(4953,667,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(4954,667,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(4955,667,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(4956,667,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(4957,667,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(4958,667,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(4959,667,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(4960,667,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(4961,667,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(4962,667,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(4963,667,'about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','BarthHaasGroup'),(4964,667,'_about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(4965,667,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas Group is the world’s largest supplier of hop products and services. The group is family owned and is active on all continents, having offices and operations in Germany, the United States, United Kingdom, Australia and China. Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group. <a href=\"www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/\"> www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/</a>'),(4966,667,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(4967,667,'about_haas','1'),(4968,667,'_about_haas','field_54e4643dd801d'),(4969,669,'_wp_attached_file','2014/12/barth-logo1.jpg'),(4970,669,