y Barth. As much as Henry Barth and John I. were the fiercest of competitors, Fred Haas was able to find common ground and, having no children of his own, saw a continuation of his company in the hands of the Barth family that started in the hop business already in 1794.'),(5128,672,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(5129,672,'about-history_2_about-history-right','The result was that in 1977, John I. Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(5130,672,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(5131,672,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(5132,672,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(5133,672,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(5134,672,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(5135,672,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5-hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters'),(5136,672,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(5137,672,'about-history_3_about-history-right','to work with commercial brewers large and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(5138,672,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(5139,672,'about-history','4'),(5140,672,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(5141,672,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(5142,672,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(5143,672,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(5144,672,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(5145,672,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(5146,672,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(5147,672,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(5148,672,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(5149,672,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(5150,672,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(5151,672,'about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','Barth Haas Group'),(5152,672,'_about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(5153,672,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas Group is the world’s largest supplier of hop products and services. The group is family owned and is active on all continents, having offices and operations in Germany, the United States, United Kingdom, Australia and China. Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group. <a href=\"www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\"> www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/</a>'),(5154,672,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(5155,672,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','669'),(5156,672,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(5157,672,'about_haas','1'),(5158,672,'_about_haas','field_54e4643dd801d'),(5159,673,'resources-header','INNOVATION, INSPIRATION AND COLLABORATION'),(5160,673,'_resources-header','field_548f4536d88a0'),(5161,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','CREATIVITY, MEET REPEATABILITY, FLEXIBILITY AND SCALABILITY.'),(5162,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(5163,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','From the one of the companies behind the HBC varieties Citra<sup>®</sup> and Mosaic<sup>®</sup> comes another advancement in creative brewing — the Haas Innovations Brewery, a world-class brewing and research facility in Yakima, Washington that gives you the ability to try out new hops, new products, new recipes and new visions in a totally controllable, repeatable and creative environment. Creating new and commercially successful beers requires access to a brewing facility that provides repeatable, flexible and scalable brewing capabilities. And that’s exactly what you get with the Innovations Brewery.'),(5164,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(5165,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','128'),(5166,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(5167,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','IMAGINE WHAT YOU COULD BREW.'),(5168,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(5169,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, we celebrate the passion and creativity of those dedicated to brewing great beer. And our research brewery is one of the ways we help that creativity happen. It starts with our sophisticated, state-of-the-art equipment and control system that allows you to refine a recipe and repeat it batch after batch. Next comes flexibility — the key to innovation. The Haas Innovations Brewery offers you a highly controlled, scientific environment in which to brew, test and adjust your recipes to get the perfect brew. Finally, there’s scalability. Our research brewery provides an unparalleled scalable brewing experience, which means you can reduce the time and uncertainty often associated with new brews and get your next brewing creation to market faster and more efficiently.'),(5170,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(5171,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','127'),(5172,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(5173,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','HERE’S TO YOUR SUCCESS'),(5174,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(5175,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, our mission is your success. Whether you’re looking to test one of our new varieties or one of your latest recipes, the Haas Innovations Brewery will help you achieve it. The Haas research brewery also allows you to test our new products and see how we can deliver the same great flavors you seek without having to use as many hops (or dollars, for that matter). In addition to giving you a place to brew, our research brewery includes a state-of-the-art laboratory that gives you the advantage of the latest hop and beer analysis technology. You also get the experience and expertise of our technical staff and brewmaster Virgil McDonald who help you get the most out of the product development process. To learn more or to reserve a brewing session, call 509-469-4000<strong>.</strong> And get ready to test, tweak, taste and toast your next great brew.'),(5176,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(5177,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','129'),(5178,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(5179,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','INNOVATIONS BREWERY FEATURES:'),(5180,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(5181,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','<ul>\r\n	<li><em>2.5 hl 5 vessel state-of-the-art brew house with 10 and 30 liter hop dosing vessels</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>A brew house control system with customizable recipe and extensive data collection</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>21 unitank fermentation and conditioning system capable of 1.25 and 2.5 hl brews</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Beer filtration capabilities including diatomaceous earth and depth filter</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Krones bottling system with double pre-evacuation &amp; CO2 pressurization</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Precision malt milling (4 roll) and adjunct preparation</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Laboratory analysis for hops and beer</em></li>\r\n</ul>'),(5182,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(5183,673,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','130'),(5184,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(5185,673,'resources-innovations-brewery','4'),(5186,673,'_resources-innovations-brewery','field_548f47c0d88a1'),(5187,673,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','HOPS. THERE’S MORE\r\nTHAN MEETS THE NOSE.'),(5188,673,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','field_548f487dd88a6'),(5189,673,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','It seems like the more you know about hops, the more there is to learn. That’s the thinking behind the Barth-Haas Hops Academy — a formal training program for brewers designed to open up a world of possibilities in the use, effects, and impact of this special brewing ingredient. In addition to helping brewers develop distinctive high-quality beers, the Hops Academy helps you improve process efficiencies and reduce waste.\r\n\r\nThe Hops Academy helps both new, experienced and even master brewers understand more about the complexities of hops and the way they interact with each other — as well as other beer ingredients — to create unique styles, flavors and aromas. To learn more about the Barth-Haas Hops Academy or to reserve a spot in an upcoming session, please visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hopsacademy.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.hopsacademy.com/en</a>'),(5190,673,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','field_548f48a2d88a7'),(5191,673,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','131'),(5192,673,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','field_548f48d8d88a8'),(5193,673,'resources-hops-academy','1'),(5194,673,'_resources-hops-academy','field_548f484fd88a5'),(5195,673,'resources-other_0_resources-other-link','http://www.asbcnet.org/Pages/default.aspx'),(5196,673,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(5197,673,'resources-other_0_resources-other-image','133'),(5198,673,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(5199,673,'resources-other_0_resources-other-header','AMERICAN SOCIETY OF BREWING CHEMISTS'),(5200,673,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(5201,673,'resources-other_0_resources-other-text','The American Society of Brewing Chemists in an internationally recognized nonprofit scientific organization founded in 1934 to improve and bring uniformity to the brewing industry on a technical level. Today, ASBC is represented by individual and corporate members worldwide representing large and small brewers, consultants, government agencies, academics, distillers, vintners and those working in allied industries.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.asbcnet.org\" >www.asbcnet.org</a>'),(5202,673,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(5203,673,'resources-other_1_resources-other-link','www.mbaa.com'),(5204,673,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(5205,673,'resources-other_1_resources-other-image','246'),(5206,673,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(5207,673,'resources-other_1_resources-other-header','MASTER BREWERS ASSOCIATION OF THE AMERICAS'),(5208,673,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(5209,673,'resources-other_1_resources-other-text','The Master Brewers Association of the Americas (MBAA) is a nonprofit professional, scientific organization dedicated to advance, support, and encourage scientific research into brewing malt beverages and related industries and to make that research available to the public through conventions, discussion groups, journals, publications and seminars.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.mbaa.com\" >www.mbaa.com</a>'),(5210,673,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(5211,673,'resources-other_2_resources-other-link','www.oregonstate.edu/foodsci'),(5212,673,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(5213,673,'resources-other_2_resources-other-image','247'),(5214,673,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(5215,673,'resources-other_2_resources-other-header','OREGON STATE UNIVERSITY'),(5216,673,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(5217,673,'resources-other_2_resources-other-text','Haas works closely in association with the Food Science and Technology section of the Oregon State University College of Agricultural Sciences.  Dr. Tom Shellhammer leads the OSU work in brewing science and technologies related to beer production and quality, in particular hop chemistry, flavor and quality.  His program is globally recognized for its efforts and achievements. \r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://oregonstate.edu/foodsci/\" >www.oregonstate.edu/foodsci/</a>\r\n<a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"http://live.oregonstate.edu/video/fermentation-science-oregon-state-university\" >www.live.oregonstate.edu/video/fermentation-science-oregon-state-university</a>'),(5218,673,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(5219,673,'resources-other_3_resources-other-link','www.usahops.org'),(5220,673,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(5221,673,'resources-other_3_resources-other-image','293'),(5222,673,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(5223,673,'resources-other_3_resources-other-header','HOP GROWERS OF AMERICA'),(5224,673,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(5225,673,'resources-other_3_resources-other-text','Hop Growers of America is a non-profit association that represents and promotes the interests of U.S. growers both domestically and internationally. As the national organization, HGA provides support, coordination and communication to growers, brewers and the world hop industry in areas of common interest, including; marketing statistics, promotion, education, and research.  \r\n<a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"http://www.usahops.org\" >www.usahops.org</a>'),(5226,673,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(5227,673,'resources-other','4'),(5228,673,'_resources-other','field_548f48e1d88a9'),(5229,674,'partners-header','HAAS. WHERE BREWING IS A TEAM SPORT'),(5230,674,'_partners-header','field_548f4f6c4dd56'),(5231,674,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-link','http://www.hopbreeding.com'),(5232,674,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-link','field_548f4fd04dd58'),(5233,674,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-image','146'),(5234,674,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-image','field_548f502d4dd59'),(5235,674,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-header','Where new beer flavors are born.'),(5236,674,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-header','field_548f50394dd5a'),(5237,674,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-text','Citra®, Mosaic®, and Equinox® — we all recognize these names as the hops behind (or, more accurately, inside) some of craft brewing’s most well known beers. But what you may not know is that these varieties were created from scratch by the Hops Breeding Company LLC, a joint venture between Haas and Select Botanicals LLC. '),(5238,674,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(5239,674,'partners-partners_0_partners-partners-more','Coming up with new aromas and flavors is a big part of what Haas contributes to the world brewing community. And one of the key contributors to these creations is our long-time master hop breeder, Gene Probasco. Gene and his agronomic team oversee more than 30 acres of experimental hops just waiting to be discovered.  The Hop Breeding Company conducts about 50 crosses of male and female hop parents each year, resulting in more than 20,000 offspring, all potentially becoming a commercial variety someday in the future.  While only a handful make it to an elite status and get christened with a name instead of a number, Gene and the Hop Breeding Company are proud parents who will stop at nothing for the good of their offspring.'),(5240,674,'_partners-partners_0_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(5241,674,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-link','http://www.lnf.com.br/'),(5242,674,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-link','field_548f4fd04dd58'),(5243,674,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-image','300'),(5244,674,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-image','field_548f502d4dd59'),(5245,674,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-header','Growing our knowledge and our reach.'),(5246,674,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-header','field_548f50394dd5a'),(5247,674,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-text','At Haas, we are always looking to enhance the quality of the hops we grow through better technology, processes and efficiencies. That’s why we partner with LNF Latino Americana. Founded in 1987 and active in various biotech industries, LNF is a family owned and operated company that was built on the commitment to deliver highly qualified technical support to companies looking for high product quality and process optimization.  '),(5248,674,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(5249,674,'partners-partners_1_partners-partners-more','The Brewing division of LNF specializes in hops and works closely with the Barth-Haas Group to develop our presence in the Brazilian market through a very close technical and commercial cooperation. '),(5250,674,'_partners-partners_1_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(5251,674,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-link','http://www.wvhops.us/index.php?p=home'),(5252,674,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-link','field_548f4fd04dd58'),(5253,674,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-image','144'),(5254,674,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-image','field_548f502d4dd59'),(5255,674,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-header',' You don’t have to be big to get Haas hops. But you do have to think big.'),(5256,674,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-header','field_548f50394dd5a'),(5257,674,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-text','Just because you’re a small brewery, doesn’t mean you shouldn’t be able to get your hands on high quality Haas hops. And thanks to our partnership with Willamette Valley Hops LLC, you can. '),(5258,674,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-text','field_548f505c4dd5b'),(5259,674,'partners-partners_2_partners-partners-more','Willamette Valley Hops is an Oregon-based family-owned premium hop distributer, which specializes in the special needs of the craft industry.  Located in the heart of Oregon’s Willamette Valley hop growing region, Bruce Wolf, the company’s founder and CEO, leads a passionate sales team and production staff to provide over 50 different domestic and foreign hop varieties to brewers worldwide. The partnership between John I. Haas and Willamette Valley Hops provides an effective and efficient means to give small brewers access to the best hops in the world.'),(5260,674,'_partners-partners_2_partners-partners-more','field_548f50724dd5c'),(5261,674,'partners-partners','3'),(5262,674,'_partners-partners','field_548f4fab4dd57'),(5263,675,'_wp_attached_file','2014/12/HPA.png'),(5264,675,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:193;s:6:\"height\";i:114;s:4:\"f