),(6324,713,'resources-header','INNOVATION, INSPIRATION AND COLLABORATION'),(6325,713,'_resources-header','field_548f4536d88a0'),(6326,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','CREATIVITY, MEET REPEATABILITY, FLEXIBILITY AND SCALABILITY.'),(6327,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(6328,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','From the one of the companies behind the HBC varieties Citra<sup>®</sup> and Mosaic<sup>®</sup> comes another advancement in creative brewing — the Haas Innovations Brewery, a world-class brewing and research facility in Yakima, Washington that gives you the ability to try out new hops, new products, new recipes and new visions in a totally controllable, repeatable and creative environment. Creating new and commercially successful beers requires access to a brewing facility that provides repeatable, flexible and scalable brewing capabilities. And that’s exactly what you get with the Innovations Brewery.'),(6329,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(6330,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','128'),(6331,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_0_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(6332,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','IMAGINE WHAT YOU COULD BREW.'),(6333,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(6334,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, we celebrate the passion and creativity of those dedicated to brewing great beer. And our research brewery is one of the ways we help that creativity happen. It starts with our sophisticated, state-of-the-art equipment and control system that allows you to refine a recipe and repeat it batch after batch. Next comes flexibility — the key to innovation. The Haas Innovations Brewery offers you a highly controlled, scientific environment in which to brew, test and adjust your recipes to get the perfect brew. Finally, there’s scalability. Our research brewery provides an unparalleled scalable brewing experience, which means you can reduce the time and uncertainty often associated with new brews and get your next brewing creation to market faster and more efficiently.'),(6335,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(6336,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','127'),(6337,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_1_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(6338,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','HERE’S TO YOUR SUCCESS'),(6339,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(6340,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','At Haas, our mission is your success. Whether you’re looking to test one of our new varieties or one of your latest recipes, the Haas Innovations Brewery will help you achieve it. The Haas research brewery also allows you to test our new products and see how we can deliver the same great flavors you seek without having to use as many hops (or dollars, for that matter). In addition to giving you a place to brew, our research brewery includes a state-of-the-art laboratory that gives you the advantage of the latest hop and beer analysis technology. You also get the experience and expertise of our technical staff and brewmaster Virgil McDonald who help you get the most out of the product development process. To learn more or to reserve a brewing session, call 509-469-4000<strong>.</strong> And get ready to test, tweak, taste and toast your next great brew.'),(6341,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(6342,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','129'),(6343,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_2_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(6344,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','INNOVATIONS BREWERY FEATURES:'),(6345,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-header','field_548f4808d88a2'),(6346,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','<ul>\r\n	<li><em>2.5 hl 5 vessel state-of-the-art brew house with 10 and 30 liter hop dosing vessels</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>A brew house control system with customizable recipe and extensive data collection</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>21 unitank fermentation and conditioning system capable of 1.25 and 2.5 hl brews</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Beer filtration capabilities including diatomaceous earth and depth filter</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Krones bottling system with double pre-evacuation &amp; CO2 pressurization</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Precision malt milling (4 roll) and adjunct preparation</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Laboratory analysis for hops and beer</em></li>\r\n</ul>'),(6347,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-text','field_548f481fd88a3'),(6348,713,'resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','130'),(6349,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery_3_resources-innovations-brewery-image','field_548f482cd88a4'),(6350,713,'resources-innovations-brewery','4'),(6351,713,'_resources-innovations-brewery','field_548f47c0d88a1'),(6352,713,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','HOPS. THERE’S MORE\r\nTHAN MEETS THE NOSE.'),(6353,713,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-header','field_548f487dd88a6'),(6354,713,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','It seems like the more you know about hops, the more there is to learn. That’s the thinking behind the Barth-Haas Hops Academy — a formal training program for brewers designed to open up a world of possibilities in the use, effects, and impact of this special brewing ingredient. In addition to helping brewers develop distinctive high-quality beers, the Hops Academy helps you improve process efficiencies and reduce waste.\r\n\r\nThe Hops Academy helps both new, experienced and even master brewers understand more about the complexities of hops and the way they interact with each other — as well as other beer ingredients — to create unique styles, flavors and aromas. To learn more about the Barth-Haas Hops Academy or to reserve a spot in an upcoming session, please visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hopsacademy.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.hopsacademy.com/en</a>'),(6355,713,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-text','field_548f48a2d88a7'),(6356,713,'resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','131'),(6357,713,'_resources-hops-academy_0_resources-hops-academy-image','field_548f48d8d88a8'),(6358,713,'resources-hops-academy','1'),(6359,713,'_resources-hops-academy','field_548f484fd88a5'),(6360,713,'resources-other_0_resources-other-link','http://www.asbcnet.org/Pages/default.aspx'),(6361,713,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(6362,713,'resources-other_0_resources-other-image','133'),(6363,713,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(6364,713,'resources-other_0_resources-other-header','AMERICAN SOCIETY OF BREWING CHEMISTS'),(6365,713,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(6366,713,'resources-other_0_resources-other-text','The American Society of Brewing Chemists in an internationally recognized nonprofit scientific organization founded in 1934 to improve and bring uniformity to the brewing industry on a technical level. Today, ASBC is represented by individual and corporate members worldwide representing large and small brewers, consultants, government agencies, academics, distillers, vintners and those working in allied industries.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.asbcnet.org\" >www.asbcnet.org</a>'),(6367,713,'_resources-other_0_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(6368,713,'resources-other_1_resources-other-link','http://www.mbaa.com'),(6369,713,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(6370,713,'resources-other_1_resources-other-image','246'),(6371,713,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(6372,713,'resources-other_1_resources-other-header','MASTER BREWERS ASSOCIATION OF THE AMERICAS'),(6373,713,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(6374,713,'resources-other_1_resources-other-text','The Master Brewers Association of the Americas (MBAA) is a nonprofit professional, scientific organization dedicated to advance, support, and encourage scientific research into brewing malt beverages and related industries and to make that research available to the public through conventions, discussion groups, journals, publications and seminars.\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.mbaa.com\" >www.mbaa.com</a>'),(6375,713,'_resources-other_1_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(6376,713,'resources-other_2_resources-other-link','http://www.oregonstate.edu/foodsci'),(6377,713,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(6378,713,'resources-other_2_resources-other-image','247'),(6379,713,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(6380,713,'resources-other_2_resources-other-header','OREGON STATE UNIVERSITY'),(6381,713,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(6382,713,'resources-other_2_resources-other-text','Haas works closely in association with the Food Science and Technology section of the Oregon State University College of Agricultural Sciences.  Dr. Tom Shellhammer leads the OSU work in brewing science and technologies related to beer production and quality, in particular hop chemistry, flavor and quality.  His program is globally recognized for its efforts and achievements. \r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://oregonstate.edu/foodsci/\" >www.oregonstate.edu/foodsci/</a>\r\n<a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"http://live.oregonstate.edu/video/fermentation-science-oregon-state-university\" >www.live.oregonstate.edu/video/fermentation-science-oregon-state-university</a>'),(6383,713,'_resources-other_2_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(6384,713,'resources-other_3_resources-other-link','http://www.usahops.org'),(6385,713,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-link','field_548f4b1ba29aa'),(6386,713,'resources-other_3_resources-other-image','293'),(6387,713,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-image','field_548f48fed88aa'),(6388,713,'resources-other_3_resources-other-header','HOP GROWERS OF AMERICA'),(6389,713,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-header','field_548f4916d88ab'),(6390,713,'resources-other_3_resources-other-text','Hop Growers of America is a non-profit association that represents and promotes the interests of U.S. growers both domestically and internationally. As the national organization, HGA provides support, coordination and communication to growers, brewers and the world hop industry in areas of common interest, including; marketing statistics, promotion, education, and research.  \r\n<a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"http://www.usahops.org\" >www.usahops.org</a>'),(6391,713,'_resources-other_3_resources-other-text','field_548f4931d88ac'),(6392,713,'resources-other','4'),(6393,713,'_resources-other','field_548f48e1d88a9'),(6394,714,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(6395,714,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(6396,714,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(6397,714,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(6398,714,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, and a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great tasting beer. \r\n\r\nAs a member of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services – Haas has the global reach to offer the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(6399,714,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(6400,714,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','625'),(6401,714,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(6402,714,'about-overview','1'),(6403,714,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(6404,714,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(6405,714,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6406,714,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(6407,714,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6408,714,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a constantly evolving company to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally come to reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(6409,714,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6410,714,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(6411,714,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6412,714,'about-history_1_about-history-header','Perseverance against all odds'),(6413,714,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6414,714,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(6415,714,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6416,714,'about-history_1_about-history-left','1914 was all but a fortunate choice of year to found a company. It was the beginning of World War I, which was followed by Prohibition and Depression – all not conducive to support a start-up hop business. But despite all odds, his business grew because of his initiative to look for customers outside the United States. In particular, John I. built strong relationships with Canadian brewers who, not surprisingly, were benefiting greatly from American Prohibition. In 1925, Haas acquired its first hop farm in the Fraser Valley of British Columbia (which eventually grew to 1,300 acres). By 1931, John I. sensed a change in what the world’s brewers were looking for. Up to that time, the most endearing quality of American hops was their low price (based on efficient farming units and strong yields) but their quality was dismal.John I. set out to change that paradigm by buying a farm in Yakima, Washington and implementing a program to reduce the seed content the picking quality of his hops.'),(6417,714,'_about-history_1_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6418,714,'about-history_1_about-history-right','In addition to his excellent timing (1933 was the repeal of Prohibition), brewers responded so favorably to his quality oriented hop farms (branded as Yakima and improve  Golding Farms) that Haas eventually became the largest private hop grower in the world with 25 farms and almost 4,000 acres.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond\" width=\"293\" height=\"149\" /></a> -->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond2\" width=\"297\" height=\"141\" /></a>'),(6419,714,'_about-history_1_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6420,714,'about-history_2_about-history-header','HAAS AND BARTH. '),(6421,714,'_about-history_2_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6422,714,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(6423,714,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6424,714,'about-history_2_about-history-left','Over the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America as it transitioned to the next generation. Fred Haas took over from John I. in 1964 and continued his quest of delivering quality hops to brewers around the world. During Fred’s time at the helm of the company, Haas expanded its product portfolio into extracts, which laid the foundation for innovative refined hop products for the next decades. It was the US processing capabilities of Haas that peeked the interest of another market leader, namely Joh. Barth &amp; Sohn, Germany, under the leadership of Henry Barth. As much as Henry Barth and John I. were the fiercest of competitors, Fred Haas was able to find common ground and, having no children of his own, saw a continuation of his company in the hands of the Barth family that started in the hop business already in 1794.'),(6425,714,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6426,714,'about-history_2_about-history-right','The result was that in 1977, John I. Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(6427,714,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6428,714,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(6429,714,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6430,714,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(6431,714,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6432,714,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large '),(6433,714,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6434,714,'about-history_3_about-history-right','and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(6435,714,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6436,714,'about-history','4'),(6437,714,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(6438,714,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(6439,714,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(6440,714,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(6441,714,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(6442,714,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-faci