for Hop Oils and Hop Aroma Products. Botanix also manufactures the full range of downstream products on behalf of the group.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.botanix.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">www.botanix.co.uk</a>'),(6750,719,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6751,719,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','676'),(6752,719,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6753,719,'about_haas_2_abt_link','http://www.botanix.co.uk'),(6754,719,'_about_haas_2_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6755,719,'about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','BetaTec'),(6756,719,'_about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6757,719,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','BetaTec Hop Products is the application arm of the Barth-Haas Group. BetaTec knows how to put the amazing natural compounds found within the hops cone to work.  BetaTec focuses on the technical support needed to apply these hop compounds to new applications that extend beyond the traditional brewing base. <a href=\"http://www.betatechopproducts.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.betatechopproducts.com</a>'),(6758,719,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6759,719,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','706'),(6760,719,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6761,719,'about_haas_3_abt_link','http://www.betatechopproducts.com'),(6762,719,'_about_haas_3_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6763,719,'about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company'),(6764,719,'_about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6765,719,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company provides hop trading and processing of domestic and imported hops and hop products to the Chinese market. <a href=\"http://www.barthhaaschina.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.barthhaaschina.com</a>'),(6766,719,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6767,719,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','678'),(6768,719,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6769,719,'about_haas_4_abt_link','http://www.barthhaaschina.com'),(6770,719,'_about_haas_4_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6771,719,'about_haas','5'),(6772,719,'_about_haas','field_54e4643dd801d'),(6773,720,'_wp_attached_file','2015/02/HPA_Logo_5.2_RGB.png'),(6774,720,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:3015;s:6:\"height\";i:1712;s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"2015/02/HPA_Logo_5.2_RGB.png\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:3:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"HPA_Logo_5.2_RGB-150x150.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"HPA_Logo_5.2_RGB-300x170.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:170;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}s:5:\"large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"HPA_Logo_5.2_RGB-1024x581.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:1024;s:6:\"height\";i:581;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:9:\"image/png\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(6775,721,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(6776,721,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(6777,721,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(6778,721,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(6779,721,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, and a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great tasting beer. \r\n\r\nAs a member of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services – Haas has the global reach to offer the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(6780,721,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(6781,721,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','625'),(6782,721,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(6783,721,'about-overview','1'),(6784,721,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(6785,721,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(6786,721,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6787,721,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(6788,721,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6789,721,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a constantly evolving company to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally come to reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(6790,721,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6791,721,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(6792,721,'_about-history_0_about-histor