"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(6808,721,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6809,721,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(6810,721,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6811,721,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(6812,721,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6813,721,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large '),(6814,721,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6815,721,'about-history_3_about-history-right','and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(6816,721,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6817,721,'about-history','4'),(6818,721,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(6819,721,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(6820,721,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(6821,721,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(6822,721,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(6823,721,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(6824,721,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(6825,721,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(6826,721,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(6827,721,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(6828,721,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(6829,721,'about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas Group'),(6830,721,'_about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6831,721,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas Group is the world’s largest supplier of hop products and services. The group is family owned and is active on all continents, having offices and operations in Germany, the United States, United Kingdom, Australia and China. Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group. <a href=\"http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\"> www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/</a>'),(6832,721,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6833,721,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','669'),(6834,721,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6835,721,'about_haas_0_abt_link','http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/'),(6836,721,'_about_haas_0_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6837,721,'about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','Hop Products Australia'),(6838,721,'_about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6839,721,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','Hop Products Australia in Hobart/Tasmania grows and processes hops for the domestic and world markets. The company pursues an intensive research programs concentrating on breeding new aroma and alpha varieties. <a href=\"http://www.hops.com.au\" target=\"_blank\">www.hops.com.au</a>'),(6840,721,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6841,721,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','720'),(6842,721,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6843,721,'about_haas_1_abt_link','http://www.hops.com.au'),(6844,721,'_about_haas_1_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6845,721,'about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','Botanix'),(6846,721,'_about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6847,721,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','Botanix, with two facilities in the United Kingdom, is the center of excellence in the group for Hop Oils and Hop Aroma Products. Botanix also manufactures the full range of downstream products on behalf of the group.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.botanix.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">www.botanix.co.uk</a>'),(6848,721,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6849,721,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','676'),(6850,721,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6851,721,'about_haas_2_abt_link','http://www.botanix.co.uk'),(6852,721,'_about_haas_2_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6853,721,'about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','BetaTec'),(6854,721,'_about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6855,721,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','BetaTec Hop Products is the application arm of the Barth-Haas Group. BetaTec knows how to put the amazing natural compounds found within the hops cone to work.  BetaTec focuses on the technical support needed to apply these hop compounds to new applications that extend beyond the traditional brewing base. <a href=\"http://www.betatechopproducts.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.betatechopproducts.com</a>'),(6856,721,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6857,721,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','706'),(6858,721,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6859,721,'about_haas_3_abt_link','http://www.betatechopproducts.com'),(6860,721,'_about_haas_3_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6861,721,'about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company'),(6862,721,'_about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6863,721,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company provides hop trading and processing of domestic and imported hops and hop products to the Chinese market. <a href=\"http://www.barthhaaschina.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.barthhaaschina.com</a>'),(6864,721,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6865,721,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','678'),(6866,721,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6867,721,'about_haas_4_abt_link','http://www.barthhaaschina.com'),(6868,721,'_about_haas_4_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6869,721,'about_haas','5'),(6870,721,'_about_haas','field_54e4643dd801d'),(6871,722,'_wp_attached_file','2015/02/Press-Release-6.19.121.pdf'),(6872,723,'_wp_attached_file','2015/02/Press-Release-June-19-2012.pdf'),(6873,724,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(6874,724,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(6875,724,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(6876,724,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(6877,724,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, and a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great tasting beer. \r\n\r\nAs a member of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services – Haas has the global reach to offer the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(6878,724,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(6879,724,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','625'),(6880,724,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(6881,724,'about-overview','1'),(6882,724,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(6883,724,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(6884,724,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6885,724,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(6886,724,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6887,724,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a constantly evolving company to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally come to reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(6888,724,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6889,724,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(6890,724,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6891,724,'about-history_1_about-history-header','Perseverance against all odds'),(6892,724,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6893,724,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(6894,724,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6895,724,'about-history_1_about-history-left','1914 was all but a fortunate choice of year to found a company. It was the beginning of World War I, which was followed by Prohibition and Depression – all not conducive to support a start-up hop business. But despite all odds, his business grew because of his initiative to look for customers outside the United States. In particular, John I. built strong relationships with Canadian brewers who, not surprisingly, were benefiting greatly from American Prohibition. In 1925, Haas acquired its first hop farm in the Fraser Valley of British Columbia (which eventually grew to 1,300 acres). By 1931, John I. sensed a change in what the world’s brewers were looking for. Up to that time, the most endearing quality of American hops was their low price (based on efficient farming units and strong yields) but their quality was dismal.John I. set out to change that paradigm by buying a farm in Yakima, Washington and implementing a program to reduce the seed content the picking quality of his hops.'),(6896,724,'_about-history_1_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6897,724,'about-history_1_about-history-right','In addition to his excellent timing (1933 was the repeal of Prohibition), brewers responded so favorably to his quality oriented hop farms (branded as Yakima and improve Golding Farms) that Haas eventually became the largest private hop grower in the world with 25 farms and almost 4,000 acres.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond\" width=\"293\" height=\"149\" /></a> -->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond2\" width=\"297\" height=\"141\" /></a>'),(6898,724,'_about-history_1_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6899,724,'about-history_2_about-history-header','HAAS AND BARTH. '),(6900,724,'_about-history_2_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6901,724,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(6902,724,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6903,724,'about-history_2_about-history-left','Over the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America as it transitioned to the next generation. Fred Haas took over from John I. in 1964 and continued his quest of delivering quality hops to brewers around the world. During Fred’s time at the helm of the company, Haas expanded its product portfolio into extracts, which laid the foundation for innovative refined hop products for the next decades. It was the US processing capabilities of Haas that peeked the interest of another market leader, namely Joh. Barth &amp; Sohn, Germany, under the leadership of Henry Barth. As much as Henry Barth and John I. were the fiercest of competitors, Fred Haas was able to find common ground and, having no children of his own, saw a continuation of his company in the hands of the Barth family that started in the hop business already in 1794.'),(6904,724,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6905,724,'about-history_2_about-history-right','The result was that in 1977, John I. Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(6906,724,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6907,724,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(6908,724,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6909,724,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(6910,724,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6911,724,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large'),(6912,724,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6913,724,'about-history_3_about-history-right','and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(6914,724,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6915,724,'about-history','4'),(6916,724,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(6917,724,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(6918,724,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(6919,724,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(6920,724,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(6921,724,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(6922,724,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(6923,724,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(6924,724,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(6925,724,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(6926,724,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(6927,724,'about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas Group'),(6928,724,'_about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6929,724,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group, the world\'s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services. The Group is family owned and is active on all continents. With offices in Germany, the United States, Australia, Switzerland, China and the United Kingdom, they are ideally placed to meet the needs of brewers, large and small, wherever they are located.\r\n\r\nBarth-Haas group is active in all parts of the supply chain from growing to recipe development and beer appreciation. Whether it be breeding or cultivation, quality assurance or the application of high performance hop products, Barth-Haas is there. <a href=\"http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\"> www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/</a>\r\n\r\nExplore the companies that make up the Barth-Haas Group.'),(6930,724,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6931,724,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','669'),(6932,724,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6933,724,'about_haas_0_abt_link','http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/'),(6934,724,'_about_haas_0_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6935,724,'about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','Hop Products Australia'),(6936,724,'_about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6937,724,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','Hop Products Australia in Hobart/Tasmania grows and processes hops for the domestic and world markets. The company pursues an intensive research programs concentrating on breeding new aroma and alpha varieties. <a href=\"http://www.hops.com.au\" target=\"_blank\">www.hops.com.au</a>'),(6938,724,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6939,724,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','720'),(6940,724,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6941,724,'about_haas_1_abt_link','http://www.hops.com.au'),(6942,724,'_about_haas_1_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6943,724,'about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','Botanix'),(6944,724,'_about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6945,724,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','Botanix, with two facilities in the United Kingdom, is the center of excellence in the group for Hop Oils and Hop Aroma Products. Botanix also manufactures the full range of downstream products on behalf of the group.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.botanix.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">www.botanix.co.uk</a>'),(6946,724,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6947,724,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','676'),(6948,724,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6949,724,'about_haas_2_abt_link','http://www.botanix.co.uk'),(6950,724,'_about_haas_2_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6951,724,'about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','BetaTec'),(6952,724,'_about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6953,724,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','BetaTec Hop Products is the application arm of the Barth-Haas Group. BetaTec knows how to put the amazing natural compounds found within the hops cone to work.  BetaTec focuses on the technical support needed to apply these hop compounds to new applications that extend beyond the traditional brewing base. <a href=\"http://www.betatechopproducts.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.betatechopproducts.com</a>'),(6954,724,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6955,724,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','706'),(6956,724,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6957,724,'about_haas_3_abt_link','http://www.betatechopproducts.com'),(6958,724,'_about_haas_3_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6959,724,'about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company'),(6960,724,'_about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(6961,724,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company provides hop trading and processing of domestic and imported hops and hop products to the Chinese market. <a href=\"http://www.barthhaaschina.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.barthhaaschina.com</a>'),(6962,724,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(6963,724,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','678'),(6964,724,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(6965,724,'about_haas_4_abt_link','http://www.barthhaaschina.com'),(6966,724,'_about_haas_4_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(6967,724,'about_haas','5'),(6968,724,'_about_haas','field_54e4643dd801d'),(6969,725,'about-overview_0_about-overview-header','HAAS. FROM HOP TO TAP'),(6970,725,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-header','field_548f0bad607eb'),(6971,725,'about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','(AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN).'),(6972,725,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-subheader','field_548f0bbd607ec'),(6973,725,'about-overview_0_about-overview-text','You could say that Haas is North America’s leading hops supplier. And that would be true. But what’s also true is that Haas is a lot more than a hops supplier. We are also a breeder, a research brewery, a loyal partner and, most of all, innovators – tireless professionals who are passionate about helping you brew great-tasting beer. \r\n\r\nAs a member of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services – Haas has the global reach to offer the products, tools, services and supply assurance you need to brew successful beers. And isn’t that why you’re here?'),(6974,725,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-text','field_548f0bef607ed'),(6975,725,'about-overview_0_about-overview-image','625'),(6976,725,'_about-overview_0_about-overview-image','field_548f0c1b607ee'),(6977,725,'about-overview','1'),(6978,725,'_about-overview','field_548f08cf607ea'),(6979,725,'about-history_0_about-history-header','THE BACKSTORY'),(6980,725,'_about-history_0_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6981,725,'about-history_0_about-history-subheader',''),(6982,725,'_about-history_0_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6983,725,'about-history_0_about-history-left','Like many of our innovative hop varieties, the history of Haas is a cross-pollination – a careful combination of people, agronomy, technology and innovation that has resulted in a constantly evolving company to meet the needs of our customers.\r\n\r\nIt all started in 1914 when young man from Britain, born to Austrian-American parents, found himself waiting tables in Nuremberg, Germany. His name was John I. Haas. One of his regular patrons was a mid-sized hop trader by the name of Mr. Bing who saw a spark in John (or John I., as his friends called him). Mr. Bing’s dream of expanding his hop business into the US would finally come to reality by engaging this energetic young man to do it. But John I.’s entrepreneurial spirit was too strong to contain and John I. soon realized that he was going to be the master of his own success and founded the company of John I. Haas, Inc.'),(6984,725,'_about-history_0_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6985,725,'about-history_0_about-history-right','<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/blackberry.jpg\" alt=\"blackberry\" width=\"377\" height=\"290\" /></a>'),(6986,725,'_about-history_0_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6987,725,'about-history_1_about-history-header','Perseverance against all odds'),(6988,725,'_about-history_1_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6989,725,'about-history_1_about-history-subheader',''),(6990,725,'_about-history_1_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6991,725,'about-history_1_about-history-left','1914 was all but a fortunate choice of year to found a company. It was the beginning of World War I, which was followed by Prohibition and Depression – all not conducive to support a start-up hop business. But despite all odds, his business grew because of his initiative to look for customers outside the United States. In particular, John I. built strong relationships with Canadian brewers who, not surprisingly, were benefiting greatly from American Prohibition. In 1925, Haas acquired its first hop farm in the Fraser Valley of British Columbia (which eventually grew to 1,300 acres). By 1931, John I. sensed a change in what the world’s brewers were looking for. Up to that time, the most endearing quality of American hops was their low price (based on efficient farming units and strong yields) but their quality was dismal.John I. set out to change that paradigm by buying a farm in Yakima, Washington and implementing a program to reduce the seed content the picking quality of his hops.'),(6992,725,'_about-history_1_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(6993,725,'about-history_1_about-history-right','In addition to his excellent timing (1933 was the repeal of Prohibition), brewers responded so favorably to his quality oriented hop farms (branded as Yakima and improve Golding Farms) that Haas eventually became the largest private hop grower in the world with 25 farms and almost 4,000 acres.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond\" width=\"293\" height=\"149\" /></a> -->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/prohibition-beyond2.jpg\" alt=\"prohibition-beyond2\" width=\"297\" height=\"141\" /></a>'),(6994,725,'_about-history_1_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(6995,725,'about-history_2_about-history-header','HAAS AND BARTH. '),(6996,725,'_about-history_2_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(6997,725,'about-history_2_about-history-subheader','FROM COMPETITORS TO COLLABORATORS'),(6998,725,'_about-history_2_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(6999,725,'about-history_2_about-history-left','Over the next 40 years, Haas maintained its leadership position in America as it transitioned to the next generation. Fred Haas took over from John I. in 1964 and continued his quest of delivering quality hops to brewers around the world. During Fred’s time at the helm of the company, Haas expanded its product portfolio into extracts, which laid the foundation for innovative refined hop products for the next decades. It was the US processing capabilities of Haas that peeked the interest of another market leader, namely Joh. Barth &amp; Sohn, Germany, under the leadership of Henry Barth. As much as Henry Barth and John I. were the fiercest of competitors, Fred Haas was able to find common ground and, having no children of his own, saw a continuation of his company in the hands of the Barth family that started in the hop business already in 1794.'),(7000,725,'_about-history_2_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(7001,725,'about-history_2_about-history-right','The result was that in 1977, John I. Haas became part of the Barth-Haas Group – the world’s leading hops supplier.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(7002,725,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(7003,725,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(7004,725,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(7005,725,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(7006,725,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(7007,725,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large'),(7008,725,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(7009,725,'about-history_3_about-history-right','and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(7010,725,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(7011,725,'about-history','4'),(7012,725,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(7013,725,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(7014,725,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(7015,725,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(7016,725,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(7017,725,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(7018,725,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(7019,725,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(7020,725,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0