wp-image-63\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/haas-brath.jpg\" alt=\"haas-brath\" width=\"296\" height=\"280\" /></a>'),(7823,752,'_about-history_2_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(7824,752,'about-history_3_about-history-header','HAAS TODAY:\r\nLEADING THE WAY INTO THE FUTURE'),(7825,752,'_about-history_3_about-history-header','field_548f0e20607f0'),(7826,752,'about-history_3_about-history-subheader',''),(7827,752,'_about-history_3_about-history-subheader','field_548f139907dda'),(7828,752,'about-history_3_about-history-left','In the years that followed, Haas maintained our passion for innovation. In the 1980’s, we began the first private hop breeding program in the industry. In the next decade, we introduced the breakthrough hop varieties Chelan and Millennium. And at the beginning of the new century, we partnered with Select Botanicals LLC to create a joint venture called the Hop Breeding Company LLC which created the highly successful varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\nToday, the John I. Haas company continues to lead the way. In 2013, Haas opened the Innovations Brewery inside our recently opened Innovations Center in Yakima, Washington. This 2.5- hectoliter research brewery has the advanced capabilities that allow our brewmasters to work with commercial brewers large'),(7829,752,'_about-history_3_about-history-left','field_548f0e74607f3'),(7830,752,'about-history_3_about-history-right','and small to develop beer formulations that utilize new hop varieties, hop products and innovative flavor concepts.\r\n\r\nIn 2014, Haas celebrated our 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary. And while a lot has changed since John I. started his hops business back in 1914, we are certain that if he were alive today, he would see the same obsession with innovation, quality and service for which he set the standard from the very beginning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-67\" src=\"http://haas.shotgunflat8.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/abt-history-logo.png\" alt=\"abt-history-logo\" width=\"361\" height=\"112\" /></a>'),(7831,752,'_about-history_3_about-history-right','field_548f0e87607f4'),(7832,752,'about-history','4'),(7833,752,'_about-history','field_548f0c37607ef'),(7834,752,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','GROWING, PICKING AND PROCESSING YOUR HOPS'),(7835,752,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-header','field_548f0ecf607f5'),(7836,752,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','While the John I. Haas company buys many of the hops we sell from high-quality partner growers in the Washington, Oregon and Idaho, we also grow, breed and harvest hops on our own farm in Yakima, Washington. The Yakima Golding Farm is home to 1,600-acres of trellised fields, harvesting facilities, hop kilns and bailing operations. It is also home to some of the most knowledgeable hop agronomy experts who put their education and passion to work in a never-ending drive for quality and efficiency. It’s been that way since John I. pioneered the world’s first seedless hop back on some of these very same fields in 1931. And it remains that way today as our team of oversees the growth of the most sought after hop varieties in the world. '),(7837,752,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-text','field_548f0ee6607f6'),(7838,752,'about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','66'),(7839,752,'_about-facilities-fields_0_about-facilities-fields-image','field_548f0efd607f7'),(7840,752,'about-facilities-fields','1'),(7841,752,'_about-facilities-fields','field_548f0e35607f1'),(7842,752,'about-team','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"205\";i:1;s:3:\"204\";i:2;s:3:\"216\";i:3;s:3:\"217\";i:4;s:3:\"218\";i:5;s:3:\"219\";i:6;s:3:\"220\";i:7;s:3:\"221\";}'),(7843,752,'_about-team','field_548f0e47607f2'),(7844,752,'about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas Group'),(7845,752,'_about_haas_0_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(7846,752,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','Haas is a proud member of the Barth-Haas Group, the world\'s largest supplier of hops, hop products and services. The Group is family owned and is active on all continents. With offices in Germany, the United States, Australia, Switzerland, China and the United Kingdom, they are ideally placed to meet the needs of brewers, large and small, wherever they are located.\r\n\r\nBarth-Haas group is active in all parts of the supply chain from growing to recipe development and beer appreciation. Whether it be breeding or cultivation, quality assurance or the application of high performance hop products, Barth-Haas is there. <a href=\"http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\"> www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/</a>\r\n\r\nExplore the companies that make up the Barth-Haas Group.'),(7847,752,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(7848,752,'about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','741'),(7849,752,'_about_haas_0_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(7850,752,'about_haas_0_abt_link','http://www.BarthHaasGroup.com/en/'),(7851,752,'_about_haas_0_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(7852,752,'about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','Hop Products Australia'),(7853,752,'_about_haas_1_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(7854,752,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','Hop Products Australia in Hobart/Tasmania grows and processes hops for the domestic and world markets. The company pursues an intensive research programs concentrating on breeding new aroma and alpha varieties. <a href=\"http://www.hops.com.au\" target=\"_blank\">www.hops.com.au</a>'),(7855,752,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(7856,752,'about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','737'),(7857,752,'_about_haas_1_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(7858,752,'about_haas_1_abt_link','http://www.hops.com.au'),(7859,752,'_about_haas_1_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(7860,752,'about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','Botanix'),(7861,752,'_about_haas_2_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(7862,752,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','Botanix, with two facilities in the United Kingdom, is the center of excellence in the group for Hop Oils and Hop Aroma Products. Botanix also manufactures the full range of downstream products on behalf of the group.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.botanix.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">www.botanix.co.uk</a>'),(7863,752,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(7864,752,'about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','736'),(7865,752,'_about_haas_2_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(7866,752,'about_haas_2_abt_link','http://www.botanix.co.uk'),(7867,752,'_about_haas_2_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(7868,752,'about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','BetaTec'),(7869,752,'_about_haas_3_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(7870,752,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','BetaTec Hop Products is the application arm of the Barth-Haas Group. BetaTec knows how to put the amazing natural compounds found within the hops cone to work.  BetaTec focuses on the technical support needed to apply these hop compounds to new applications that extend beyond the traditional brewing base. <a href=\"http://www.betatechopproducts.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.betatechopproducts.com</a>'),(7871,752,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_text','field_54e464e4d801f'),(7872,752,'about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','735'),(7873,752,'_about_haas_3_abt_haas_img','field_54e46b3fd56a0'),(7874,752,'about_haas_3_abt_link','http://www.betatechopproducts.com'),(7875,752,'_about_haas_3_abt_link','field_54e718cfb4c04'),(7876,752,'about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company'),(7877,752,'_about_haas_4_abt_hass_header','field_54e4647ed801e'),(7878,752,'about_haas_4_abt_haas_text','Barth-Haas (Beijing) Trade Company provides hop trading and processing of domestic and imported hops and hop products to the Chinese market. <a href=\"http://www.barthhaaschina.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.barthhaaschina.com</a>'),(7879,752,'_about_haas_4_abt_haas_text'