w.johnihaas.com/contact/rhombusbrewergmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05202015/',0,'contact','',0),(866,1,'2015-05-20 02:25:39','2015-05-20 02:25:39','','rhombusbrewer@gmail.com submitted an inquiry on 05/20/2015','','publish','open','open','','rhombusbrewergmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05202015-2','','','2015-05-20 02:25:39','2015-05-20 02:25:39','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/rhombusbrewergmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05202015-2/',0,'contact','',0),(867,1,'2015-05-21 06:00:40','2015-05-21 06:00:40','','michele.biofinmalt@gmail.com submitted an inquiry on 05/21/2015','','publish','open','open','','michele-biofinmaltgmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05212015','','','2015-05-21 06:00:40','2015-05-21 06:00:40','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/michele-biofinmaltgmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05212015/',0,'contact','',0),(868,8,'2015-05-21 16:14:44','2015-05-21 16:14:44','The explosion in the craft beer industry has placed an incredible demand on the hops industry. This is especially true with the popularity of the India Pale Ale (IPA) beer style whose primary flavor characteristic is from hops…a lot of hops — in most cases ten times more hops per barrel than the average beer!\r\n\r\nWith craft brewing growing at about 15% volume per year, the impact on hop demand is a magnitude greater. So what’s a hop company to do? How do we not simply react, but be proactive as well? And I do mean ‘we’ because, as much as we compete with other hop companies, it is best for all of us if we are all in sync with what our brewers need. Here are some of the steps Haas is taking to meet the demand of our customers.\r\n\r\n<strong>More hop acreage</strong>\r\n\r\nIt may seem obvious but it isn\'t always easy. In addition to the land needed to meet the demand for these popular craft hop varieties, we also need to be certain of sufficient irrigation as well as increased processing capacity to provide the supply assurance vital to our customers.\r\n\r\n<strong>More accessibility to hops</strong>\r\n\r\nAnother change brought about by the craft beer boom is, of course, the number of breweries demanding these flavor-laden hops — now approaching 4,000 in the U.S. alone. To meet the need of a greater number of brewers and the smaller order sizes involved, Haas collaborates with Willamette Valley Hops as a channel partner out of Oregon to ensure brewers have access to the hops they need to succeed.\r\n\r\n<strong>More hop varieties</strong>\r\n\r\nIn addition to meeting the demand for more hops and greater accessibility, craft brewers have an insatiable thirst for new hop varieties with bold and distinctive hop flavors. Robust fruity and citrus flavors, such as apricot, strawberry, melon, kiwi fruit, and even coconut, are now in the forefront of hop variety development — and a big part of the Haas hop breeding efforts. In fact, Haas is part of the Hop Breeding Company LLC, sharing equally in a joint venture with Select Botanicals LLC which has been instrumental in the development of the vastly popular hop varieties Citra®, Mosaic® and Equinox™.\r\n\r\n<strong>More to come</strong>\r\n\r\nWho knows where this hopsession (sorry, I couldn’t resist) with flavor will take the craft industry. But one thing I know for certain is that Haas will be doing our best to deliver the hops, hop products, supply assurance, technical support and innovations brewers need to succeed. Our new BBC Pure Hop Pellet we introduced at CBC is a good example of that. But that deserves its own blog post. Stay tuned!','Hops. The ‘fruit’ of our labor','With craft brewing growing at about 15% volume per year, the impact on hop demand is a magnitude greater. So what’s a hop company to do? How do we not simply react, but be proactive as well? And I do mean ‘we’ because, as much as we compete with other hop companies, it is best for all of us if we are all in sync with what our brewers need. Here are some of the steps Haas is taking to meet the demand of our customers.','draft','open','open','','hops-the-fruit-of-our-labor','','','2015-05-21 16:15:22','2015-05-21 16:15:22','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/?post_type=blog&#038;p=868',0,'blog','',0),(870,6,'2015-05-21 16:08:09','2015-05-21 16:08:09','','MMP_395s','','inherit','open','open','','mmp_395s','','','2015-05-21 16:08:09','2015-05-21 16:08:09','',868,'http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/MMP_395s.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(872,1,'2015-05-21 21:16:29','2015-05-21 21:16:29','','dan@dokndan.com submitted an inquiry on 05/21/2015','','publish','open','open','','dandokndan-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05212015','','','2015-05-21 21:16:29','2015-05-21 21:16:29','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/dandokndan-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05212015/',0,'contact','',0),(873,1,'2015-05-22 15:33:07','2015-05-22 15:33:07','','Iancrane36@gmail.com submitted an inquiry on 05/22/2015','','publish','open','open','','iancrane36gmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015','','','2015-05-22 15:33:07','2015-05-22 15:33:07','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/iancrane36gmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015/',0,'contact','',0),(874,1,'2015-05-22 20:08:15','2015-05-22 20:08:15','','contato@expressotransbrasil.com.br submitted an inquiry on 05/22/2015','','publish','open','open','','contatoexpressotransbrasil-com-br-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015','','','2015-05-22 20:08:15','2015-05-22 20:08:15','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/contatoexpressotransbrasil-com-br-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015/',0,'contact','',0),(875,1,'2015-05-22 20:08:15','2015-05-22 20:08:15','','contato@expressotransbrasil.com.br submitted an inquiry on 05/22/2015','','publish','open','open','','contatoexpressotransbrasil-com-br-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015','','','2015-05-22 20:08:15','2015-05-22 20:08:15','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/contatoexpressotransbrasil-com-br-submitted-an-inquiry-on-05222015/',0,'contact','',0),(876,1,'2015-05-22 20:08:16','2015-05-22 20:08:16','