 the Hallertau region of Germany), and if you haven’t experienced the awesomeness of exploring a fully mature hop “garden” or seen hop harvesting in action, you’re in for a real experience. But the Hops Academy course is not just tours of hop fields, harvesting, and social events. It is designed as an introductory educational foray into hops and provides enough technical depth to provide a deeper look into the workings of <em>Humulus lupulus</em>, and why hops are so unique and important for brewers. Specialists from both the U.S. and Germany will be there to give insights into the different aspects of hops and brewing including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hop botany and cultivation</li>\r\n	<li>Breeding and new variety development</li>\r\n	<li>Hop products and their applications, including pellets, CO2 extract, even advanced products</li>\r\n	<li>Hop chemistry, quality, and sensory analysis, of both hops and beer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDon’t worry about the chemistry if you’re not a brewing geek – some of the information may be over your head, but you won’t be overwhelmed. And much of the insight you gain will help you understand and appreciate the benefits and hops and how to best utilize them to your advantage. However, if you <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">are</span> technically savvy, you won’t be bored. You can interact with highly knowledgeable experts who can help you with any of your questions or issues regarding hops and beer.\r\n\r\nTo best provide an intimate experience, this Hops Academy program in Yakima will be a small group, limited to just 30 participants. In addition, our aim for the program is to be not just educational but entertaining with some fun built in … including our evening BBQ at the Haas traditional Bavarian beer garden.\r\n\r\nRegistration is $350. As I mentioned, space is limited and we’re only weeks away. Inquire directly to me at <a href=\"mailto:tim.kostelecky@johnihaas.com\">tim.kostelecky@johnihaas.com</a> for further information and to register for the course. And for more information about the Barth-Haas Hops Academy, visit <a href=\"http://www.hopsacademy.com\">www.hopsacademy.com</a>. Hope to see you in Yakima.\r\n\r\nTim Kostelecky\r\nHops &amp; Brewing Technical Specialist\r\nJohn I. Haas, Inc. – Yakima WA\r\n509-469-4050','Join us for the Hops Academy in August','','publish','open','open','','join-us-for-the-hops-academy-in-august','','','2015-07-08 22:23:44','2015-07-08 22:23:44','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/?post_type=blog&#038;p=946',0,'blog','',0),(947,6,'2015-07-08 18:46:59','2015-07-08 18:46:59','','Mallott - Hop Sniff (2)','','inherit','open','open','','mallott-hop-sniff-2','','','2015-07-08 18:46:59','2015-07-08 18:46:59','',946,'http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Mallott-Hop-Sniff-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(949,1,'2015-07-09 19:06:04','2015-07-09 19:06:04','','inovarepromocional@gmail.com submitted an inquiry on 07/9/2015','','publish','open','open','','inovarepromocionalgmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-0792015','','','2015-07-09 19:06:04','2015-07-09 19:06:04','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/inovarepromocionalgmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-0792015/',0,'contact','',0),(950,1,'2015-07-10 14:25:16','2015-07-10 14:25:16','','alexander.cola@universallocacoes.com submitted an inquiry on 07/10/2015','','publish','open','open','','alexander-colauniversallocacoes-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-07102015','','','2015-07-10 14:25:16','2015-07-10 14:25:16','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/alexander-colauniversallocacoes-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-07102015/',0,'contact','',0),(951,1,'2015-07-11 18:47:29','2015-07-11 18:47:29','','appollosheila1@gmail.com submitted an inquiry on 07/11/2015','','publish','open','open','','appollosheila1gmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-07112015','','','2015-07-11 18:47:29','2015-07-11 18:47:29','',0,'http://www.johnihaas.com/contact/appollosheila1gmail-com-submitted-an-inquiry-on-07112015/',0,'contact','',0),(952,1