community. &lt;pictured: John Gorman, Sr. Director of Sales for John I. Haas, Inc. with Rick Phillips, Executive Director, and Sara Holtzinger, Director Development, of the Union Gospel Mission&gt;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1080\" src=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/UGM-240x300.jpg\" alt=\"UGM\" width=\"240\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nPerry Technical Institute\r\nAs a local employer, Haas appreciates the excellent training programs offered by the Perry Technical Institute.  A donation was recently made to be used toward the purchase of equipment for their Instrumentation and Industrial Automation Technology program.  This program is scheduled to be housed in a brand new facility on the Perry Tech campus. &lt;pictured: Scott Hoffine, Haas CO2 Plant Operations Manager (and Perry Tech graduate) and Joe Stark, VP of Haas Manufacturing, with Erin Fishburn, Foundation Director for Perry Technical Institute&gt;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1079\" src=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Perry-Tech-285x300.jpg\" alt=\"Perry Tech\" width=\"285\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nCitizens for Safe Yakima Valley Communities\r\nIt is the mission of the Citizens for Save Yakima Valley Communities (CSC) to help provide a safe place to live, work, and raise a family by focusing on individual problems currently facing our city of Yakima and the surrounding valley.  Haas has made a monetary donation to CSC for their Graffiti Solution Program, helping to remove and prevent the occurrence of graffiti in the community. &lt;pictured:  Carmen Mendez, Director of CSC, and Pete Mahony, VP of Supply Chain Management and Purchasing for John I. Haas, Inc.&gt;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1077\" src=\"http://www.johnihaas.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/CSC_1251-300x273.jpg\" alt=\"CSC_1251\" width=\"300\" height=\"273\" />','HAAS SUPPORTS THE YAKIMA COMMUNITY','','draft','closed','closed','','',''